# Frontend Coding Standards

## State Management Split — Strict Rule

**TanStack Query** owns all server state. **Zustand** owns all client state. Never mix.

```typescript
// GOOD — server state in TanStack Query
function useReviews(repoId: string) {
  return useQuery({
    queryKey: ['reviews', repoId],
    queryFn: () => reviewsApi.list(repoId),
  });
}

// GOOD — client state in Zustand
const useAuthStore = create<AuthState>((set) => ({
  user: null,
  token: null,
  setUser: (user) => set({ user }),
}));

// BAD — API data in Zustand
const useReviewStore = create((set) => ({
  reviews: [],
  fetchReviews: async () => { /* ❌ wrong layer */ },
}));
```

---

## Feature Boundary Rule — No Cross-Feature Imports

Features must not import from each other. Cross-feature data goes through `shared/types/api.ts`.

```typescript
// BAD — reviews feature importing auth hook
import { useAuth } from '../auth/hooks/useAuth';  // ❌

// GOOD — read from shared store
import { useAuthStore } from '@/features/auth/store/authStore';  // ✅ shared store
// OR pass as prop from a parent layout component
```

Every feature is self-contained:
```
features/reviews/
  pages/         ← route-level components
  components/    ← feature-scoped UI
  hooks/         ← TanStack Query hooks
  api/           ← axios calls (only place fetch/axios is used)
```

---

## API Module Pattern — No fetch() Outside api/

```typescript
// GOOD — all HTTP in the api/ module
// features/reviews/api/reviewsApi.ts
export const reviewsApi = {
  list: (repoId: string, page = 1) =>
    apiClient.get<PaginatedResponse<ReviewSummaryDTO>>('/reviews', { params: { repo_id: repoId, page } }),

  getById: (id: string) =>
    apiClient.get<ReviewDetailDTO>(`/reviews/${id}`),
};

// GOOD — hook uses api module
// features/reviews/hooks/useReviews.ts
export function useReviews(repoId: string) {
  return useQuery({ queryKey: ['reviews', repoId], queryFn: () => reviewsApi.list(repoId) });
}

// BAD — fetch directly in component
function ReviewList() {
  const [reviews, setReviews] = useState([]);
  useEffect(() => {
    fetch('/api/v1/reviews').then(...)  // ❌ never
  }, []);
}
```

`apiClient` is the shared axios instance in `shared/utils/apiClient.ts` that:
- Sets `Authorization: Bearer <token>` from Zustand auth store
- Handles 401 → clears auth and redirects to login
- Has base URL from `config/env.ts`

---

## Environment Variables — Always via config/env.ts

```typescript
// GOOD
import { env } from '@/config/env';
const url = env.VITE_API_BASE_URL;

// BAD
const url = import.meta.env.VITE_API_BASE_URL;  // ❌ no type safety, scattered

// BAD
const url = 'http://localhost:8000';  // ❌ hardcoded
```

`config/env.ts` exports a typed, validated env object.

---

## TypeScript — Strict Mode, No `any`

```typescript
// BAD
const handleData = (data: any) => { ... }  // ❌

// GOOD
const handleData = (data: ReviewDetailDTO) => { ... }  // ✅

// Acceptable with justification
const legacy = response.data as any; // TODO: type after backend adds schema  ✅ comment required
```

Use `unknown` instead of `any` when the type is genuinely unknown — then narrow with type guards.
All shared API response types live in `shared/types/api.ts` mirroring backend DTOs.

---

## Component Patterns

```typescript
// GOOD — named export, colocated with feature
export function ReviewCard({ review }: { review: ReviewSummaryDTO }) {
  return <div>...</div>;
}

// GOOD — loading/error handled at the hook call site, not deep in tree
function ReviewsPage() {
  const { data, isLoading, error } = useReviews(repoId);
  if (isLoading) return <Spinner />;
  if (error) return <ErrorState message="Failed to load reviews" />;
  return <ReviewList reviews={data.items} />;
}

// BAD — default export from deep inside a file
export default function () { ... }  // ❌ harder to refactor/search
```

No class components. All components are function components.
No prop drilling more than 2 levels — use context or shared store.

---

## Mutation Pattern (TanStack Query)

```typescript
// GOOD — optimistic update or invalidate on success
function useUpdateAgentConfig(repoId: string) {
  const queryClient = useQueryClient();
  return useMutation({
    mutationFn: (config: UpdateAgentConfigRequest) => repositoriesApi.updateConfig(repoId, config),
    onSuccess: () => queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['repos', repoId, 'config'] }),
    onError: (err) => toast.error('Failed to update config'),
  });
}
```

Never use `useState` + `useEffect` + `fetch` for data fetching. Always use TanStack Query.

---

## Naming Conventions

| Thing | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Components | `PascalCase.tsx` | `ReviewCard.tsx` |
| Hooks | `use` prefix, `camelCase.ts` | `useReviews.ts` |
| API modules | `camelCase + Api.ts` | `reviewsApi.ts` |
| Stores | `camelCase + Store.ts` | `authStore.ts` |
| Types/interfaces | `PascalCase` | `ReviewDetailDTO` |
| Page components | `PascalCase + Page.tsx` | `ReviewDetailPage.tsx` |

---

## Tooling

```bash
# Type check (no emit)
npx tsc --noEmit

# Lint
npx eslint frontend/src/

# Tests
npx vitest run

# All checks
npm run check
```

`tsc`, `eslint`, and `vitest` must pass with zero new errors before any commit.
